    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="original">
                <p>Relacja <persName ref="#ehri_et_schaechter_fischer" type="ehri">Fischela Schaechtera</persName> (sygn. 301/201) </p>
                <p>Maszynopis, 1 strona, 210 x 295 mm, język polski </p>
                <p><pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010201_01.jpg" n="1"/><persName ref="#ehri_et_schaechter_fischer" type="ehri">Fischel Schaechter</persName>,
                        <term ref="#t822" type="subject">syn</term>
                    <persName ref="#ehri_et_schaechter_eliasz" type="ehri">Eljasza</persName></p>
                <p>Urodzony <date when="1933-05-22">22.5.1933 rok</date> w <placeName ref="#berehove" type="ehri">Beregsas</placeName><note
                        type="gloss">Właściwie: Beregszasz, obecnie Berehowo (Ukraina)</note> (<placeName ref="#hungary" type="ehri"
                    >Węgry</placeName>)</p>
                <p>W roku <date when="1942">1942</date> został wraz z <term ref="#t822" type="subject">rodziną</term>
                    <term ref="#t518" type="subject">wysiedlony</term> do polskiej <placeName ref="#ukraine" type="ehri">Ukrainy</placeName>. Przeżył
                        <term ref="#t532" type="subject">zastrzelenia</term> Żydów w <placeName ref="#halych" type="ehri">Haliczu</placeName>, <term
                        ref="#t346" type="subject">pogrom</term> w <placeName ref="#ivano-frankivsk" type="ehri">Stanisławowie</placeName>. Następnie
                    przez jakiś rok wędrował wraz z <term ref="#t822" type="subject">rodziną</term> z jednej miejscowości do drugiej, jako <placeName
                        ref="#ukraine" type="ehri">Ukraińcy</placeName>. W połowie roku <date when="1943">1943</date> przybyli do <placeName
                        ref="#vynohradiv" type="ehri">Nagymzolos</placeName>. <note type="gloss">właściwie: Nagyszöllos, obecnie Winohradow
                        (Ukraina)</note> Tam się ukrywali jako <term ref="#t373" type="subject">aryjczycy</term> aż do czasu utworzenia <term
                        ref="#t545" type="subject">getta</term>, które zostało utworzone nazajutrz po przybyciu <term ref="#t1159" type="subject"
                        >Niemców</term> do miasteczka. W <date when="1944-05">maju 1944</date> przybył do <placeName ref="#l2" type="camp">Oświęcimia
                        (Brzezinki</placeName>). Numer wytatuowany A 5107. Zaraz po przybyciu jego z <term ref="#t822" type="subject">bratem</term>
                    jako <term ref="#t822" type="subject">bliźniaków</term> odstawiono na bok, do <term ref="#t491" type="subject">szpitala
                        (Krankenbau)</term>. 9 razy <term ref="#t495" type="subject">odciągnęli</term> mu krew, <term ref="#t495" type="subject"
                        >mierzono</term> paznokcie, mierzono wszystkie części pod nadzorem <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">SS</term>
                    <foreign xml:lang="de">Obersturmführera – Lagerarzta</foreign>. <note type="gloss"><foreign xml:lang="de">SS
                            Obersturmführer</foreign> – nadporucznik; <foreign xml:lang="de">Lagerarzt</foreign> – lekarz obozowy</note> Wiele <term
                        ref="#t822" type="subject">bliźniaków</term> (przeważnie dziewczęta) zmarło po tych <term ref="#t495" type="subject"
                        >zabiegach</term>. <term ref="#t822" type="subject">Bliźniacy</term> nie otrzymali nawet normalnej <term ref="#t834"
                        type="subject">racji żywnościowej</term> i musieli ciężko <term ref="#t556" type="subject">pracować</term> przy
                    kamieniach.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="transcription">
                <p><pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010201_01.jpg" n="1"/><persName ref="#ehri_et_schaechter_fischer" type="ehri">Fischer Schaechter</persName>
                    Testimony (doc. 301/201)</p>
                <p>Typescript, 1 page, 210 x 295 mm, Polish language</p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_schaechter_fischer" type="ehri">Fischer Schaechter</persName>, <term ref="#t822" type="subject">son</term>
                    of <persName ref="#ehri_et_schaechter_eliasz" type="ehri">Eliasz</persName>.</p>
                <p>Born on <date when="1933-05-22">May 22, 1933</date> in <placeName ref="#berehove" type="ehri">Beregsas</placeName> (<placeName
                        ref="#hungary" type="ehri">Hungary</placeName>). <note type="gloss">Beregszasz, today Berehovo (Ukraine)</note></p>
                <p>In <date when="1942">1942</date>, he was <term ref="#t518" type="subject">deported</term> with his <term ref="#t822" type="subject"
                        >family</term> to Polish <placeName ref="#ukraine" type="ehri">Ukraine</placeName>. He survived the <term ref="#t532"
                        type="subject">shootings</term> of Jews in <placeName ref="#halych" type="ehri">Halicz</placeName>, a <term ref="#t346"
                        type="subject">pogrom</term> in <placeName ref="#ivano-frankivsk" type="ehri">Stanisławów</placeName>. Then, for a year or so,
                    he wandered with his <term ref="#t822" type="subject">family</term> from one place to another, as <term
                        ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians" type="subject">Ukrainians</term>. In mid-<date when="1943">1943</date> they arrived in
                        <placeName ref="#vynohradiv" type="ehri">Nagymzolos</placeName>. <note type="gloss">Nagyszöllos, today Vinohradiv
                        (Ukraine).</note> They lived there as <term ref="#t373" type="subject">Aryans</term> until the <term ref="#t545"
                        type="subject">ghetto</term> was created one day after the <term ref="#t1159" type="subject">Germans</term> arrived in the
                    town. In <date when="1944-05">May 1944</date> he arrived at <placeName ref="#l2" type="camp">Oświęcim [Auschwitz]
                        (Brzezinka)</placeName>. A tattooed <term ref="#t411" type="subject">number</term> A 5107. Right after he arrived there with
                    his <term ref="#t822" type="subject">brother</term>, as twins they were sent aside, to the <term ref="#t491" type="subject"
                        >hospital (Krankenbau)</term>. Nine times his blood was <term ref="#t495" type="subject">drawn</term>, his nails were <term
                        ref="#t495" type="subject">measured</term>, all parts of his body were measured under the supervision of <foreign
                        xml:lang="de">Obersturmführer – Lagerarzt</foreign>
                    <note type="gloss">Oberstürmführer – SS rank equal to Oberleutnant (lieutenant). Lagerarzt (German) – camp doctor. Research on
                        twins was made by infamous doctor Josef Mengele, having the rank of Hauptstürmführer (captain).</note> Many <term ref="#t822"
                        type="subject">twins</term>, (mostly girls) died after these <term ref="#t495" type="subject">experiments</term>. The <term
                        ref="#t822" type="subject">twin brothers</term> did not even receive regular <term ref="#t834" type="subject">food
                        rations</term> and had to <term ref="#t943" type="subject">work</term> hard [moving] stones.</p>
            </div>
